# Design System Inspired by Lulo Bank

## 1. Visual Theme & Atmosphere

Lulo Bank's design system embodies modern fintech accessibility with a bold, energetic personality. The interface balances professional financial credibility with youthful vibrancy through strategic use of electric lime accents against deep navy foundations. The design language is clean and spacious, prioritizing clarity and user confidence through generous whitespace, refined typography, and purposeful color contrast. Dark-mode dominance creates a premium, contemporary feel while the electric yellow accent (Lulo Green) serves as a high-energy call-to-action element that signals opportunity and financial growth. The overall aesthetic is minimalist yet approachable, designed to demystify banking and make financial services feel friendly and achievable.

**Key Characteristics**
- Deep navy and charcoal primary palette with high contrast against neutral backgrounds
- Electric lime (`#E8FF00`) accent for primary CTAs and positive financial messaging
- Generous spacing and breathing room throughout layouts
- Bold, geometric typography using Gilroy font family
- Soft, distant shadows creating subtle depth without visual clutter
- Rounded interactive elements (buttons, cards) for approachability
- Mobile-first responsive strategy with touch-friendly targets
- Semantic color coding for financial states and user feedback

## 2. Color Palette & Roles

### Primary
- **Deep Navy** (`#121622`): Primary surface color for headers, navigation, and high-contrast sections; used for text and background throughout the interface
- **Navy Shade** (`#1B2132`): Secondary dark surface; used for elevated sections, cards, and container backgrounds to create subtle depth variation

### Accent Colors
- **Electric Lime** (`#E8FF00`): Primary accent and CTA button color; signals positive actions, financial gains, and interactive elements; used for floating action buttons and highlight states
- **Sky Blue** (`#79CFFF`): Accent for secondary messaging; used sparingly for informational callouts and design highlights

### Interactive
- **Slate Blue** (`#2B3550`): Interactive component background; used for secondary buttons, form fields, and disabled states
- **Slate Muted** (`#667A99`): Tertiary interactive element; used for inactive states and lower-priority actions
- **Charcoal Link** (`#121722`): Link and navigation text; provides clickable element distinction

### Neutral Scale
- **Pure Black** (`#000000`): Primary text color for all body copy; ensures maximum readability and accessibility
- **Pure White** (`#FFFFFF`): Inverse text on dark backgrounds; primary background for light mode sections and card surfaces
- **Light Gray** (`#DFE2E7`): Tertiary text and subtle dividers; used for secondary information and border treatments
- **Off White** (`#F4F4F4`): Subtle background fill; minimal contrast background for grouping related content

### Surface & Borders
- **Slate Border** (`#BDC9DB`): Border and divider color; provides subtle visual separation without distraction
- **Navy Background** (`#1A2032`): Deep background surface variant; used as alternative primary background in dark-mode sections

## 3. Typography Rules

### Font Family
- **Primary: Gilroy Bold** (`gilroy-bold`): Fallback stack `Gilroy, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif`
- **Secondary: Gilroy Regular** (`gilroy-regular`): Fallback stack `Gilroy, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif`

### Hierarchy

| Role | Font | Size | Weight | Line Height | Letter Spacing | Notes |
|------|------|------|--------|-------------|----------------|-------|
| Display XL | Gilroy Bold | 40px | 400 | 44px | 0 | Hero headlines; primary page titles |
| Heading Large | Gilroy Regular | 38.4px | 400 | 42.24px | 0 | Section headers; major content divisions |
| Heading Medium | Gilroy Bold | 19.2px | 400 | 19.2px | 0 | Subsection headers; card titles |
| Body Primary | Gilroy Regular | 14px | 400 | 16.8px | 0 | Main content copy; standard paragraph text |
| Body Secondary | Gilroy Regular | 16px | 400 | 16px | 0 | Supporting copy; feature descriptions |
| Label / Button | Gilroy Bold | 16px | 400 | 16px | 0 | Button text; form labels; navigation items |
| Caption | Gilroy Bold | 14.4px | 400 | 14.4px | 0 | Fine print; helper text; metadata |
| Link | Gilroy Regular | 16px | 400 | 16px | 0 | Hyperlink text; navigation links |

### Principles
- Font weight is consistently `400` (regular) across all sizes; emphasis achieved through size and color contrast rather than weight variation
- Line height set to 110–120% of font size for optimal readability and visual rhythm
- Generous letter spacing not applied; relies on font geometry for clarity
- Hierarchy established through size jumps and semantic color roles rather than excessive weight variation
- All fonts default to screen-optimized rendering; use `-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased` for crisp appearance
- Maintain minimum 14px for body text to ensure accessibility on mobile devices

